nd":"text","text":"of sheep or goats; (Msb;) and of camels: (Idem in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rwH","text_ar":"روح"},{"kind":"text","text":":) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^owK","text_ar":"مَاْوٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used peculiarly in relation to camels: (S;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^owiY AlA_ibili","text_ar":"مَاْوِى الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^owaY AlA_ibili","text_ar":"مَاْوَى الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but anomalous, (Fr, T, S, Msb,) and the only instance of the kind except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^oqiY AlEayoni","text_ar":"مَاْقِى العَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Fr, T, M: [but see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA^q","text_ar":"ماق"},{"kind":"text","text":":])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^owaY","text_ar":"مَاْوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^oq","text_ar":"مُوْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^oq","text_ar":"مَاْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the forms preferred: (Fr, T:) [Az also says,] I have heard the chaste in speech of the Benoo-Kiláb use, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^owaY AlA_ibili","text_ar":"مَاْوَى الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the word ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^owaAp","text_ar":"مَاْوَاة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jan~apu AlmaA^owaY","text_ar":"جَنَّةُ المَاْوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [liii. 15], is said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The paradise to which repair the souls of the martyrs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Bd, Jel, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the angels:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that in which the night is passed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","Fr","T","Bd","Jel","TA"]}]}}